WEBVTT

00:00:06.141 --> 00:00:09.621
That self-defense gadget, the stun gun,
has somehow become a sport.

00:00:10.521 --> 00:00:14.081
Tonight, a new martial art will be born.

00:00:14.781 --> 00:00:21.662
Sports Stun Gun.
And we're off.

00:00:21.982 --> 00:00:26.062
I'm your tournament commissioner, Osamu
Shitara. Nice to meet you.

00:00:26.082 --> 00:00:28.182
What is this, guys?
Right?

00:00:28.652 --> 00:00:29.652
Huh?
Do your best.

00:00:29.842 --> 00:00:34.543
We're starting with Sports Stun Gun?
This is the first I've heard of it.

00:00:35.623 --> 00:00:36.623
Huh?
W-W-Wait, what?

00:00:36.803 --> 00:00:39.723
Whoa!
Hold on.

00:00:39.723 --> 00:00:43.364
Whoa!
It's real.

00:00:44.504 --> 00:00:46.024
It's real.
It's real.

00:00:46.124 --> 00:00:47.784
There it is.
Okay, okay, okay.

00:00:47.904 --> 00:00:49.364
This is insane.
Insane.

00:00:49.664 --> 00:00:51.684
So, as you can see...
As you can see...

00:00:51.684 --> 00:00:56.425
People are scared of stun guns.
Naturally.

00:00:57.385 --> 00:00:58.785
Right.
People are scared of them.

00:00:59.005 --> 00:01:02.845
That was terrifying.
But why not turn it into a sport?

00:01:02.965 --> 00:01:06.786
How do you make that a sport?
But you're all dressed for it already,

00:01:07.006 --> 00:01:09.906
so you came here knowing you'd do it.
No we didn't.

00:01:09.906 --> 00:01:10.966
We didn't.
We didn't.

00:01:10.966 --> 00:01:15.426
Well, anyway... Honestly, I think this is
a simple, easy-to-follow event.

00:01:15.906 --> 00:01:17.846
The rules are simple.
Really simple.

00:01:17.886 --> 00:01:23.487
It's one-on-one, and whoever gets stunned
loses. That's right.

00:01:24.227 --> 00:01:29.287
I'm already 48, you know.
I'm not that much younger.

00:01:29.747 --> 00:01:32.288
I'm 48 too.
Oh, 48?

00:01:32.448 --> 00:01:35.608
We even have the same birthday, May 27.
What?!

00:01:35.628 --> 00:01:40.288
May 27.
Oh, happy birthday.

00:01:40.688 --> 00:01:43.749
Careful, careful.
Careful, careful.

00:01:43.829 --> 00:01:50.209
Careful, careful.
This is scary as hell.

00:01:50.249 --> 00:01:53.549
Let go of me.
It's not just a little zap.

00:01:53.589 --> 00:01:56.270
So, with that...

00:01:56.610 --> 00:02:00.830
Today these eight comedians will face off
in a tournament.

00:02:02.750 --> 00:02:08.731
Only the winner gets to leave the venue
without being stunned even once.

00:02:08.731 --> 00:02:12.771
First up, in the opening round...

00:02:15.451 --> 00:02:22.192
Minamikawa vs. Omiokuri Geinin Shinichi.
Kickboxing, jiu-jitsu...

00:02:23.392 --> 00:02:29.072
And Krav Maga too,
that Israeli close-combat style,

00:02:29.072 --> 00:02:31.673
and Systema.
I've trained in MMA too,

00:02:32.773 --> 00:02:36.073
so in terms of fighting another person,

00:02:36.873 --> 00:02:38.933
I think I'm more used to it than the
others.

00:02:39.373 --> 00:02:42.674
I think I can land it with speed.

00:02:43.834 --> 00:02:48.474
I'm still only 39, and I can run the 50
meters in the 6-second range.

00:02:49.714 --> 00:02:52.974
So I think I can use that.

00:02:54.175 --> 00:02:59.655
And now an unprecedented sport is about to
begin. I'll be on play-by-play, Shigeki Seino.

00:02:59.655 --> 00:03:00.798
Thank you very much.
Yep.

00:03:01.455 --> 00:03:06.556
We're about to begin the first match of
round one. This time it's Minamikawa vs. Shinichi.

00:03:06.556 --> 00:03:08.216
A great matchup right out of the gate.
Absolutely.

00:03:08.736 --> 00:03:13.041
This is the very first Sports Stun Gun
match.

00:03:13.041 --> 00:03:17.116
No one has ever seen one before,
so this is the one to watch.

00:03:17.196 --> 00:03:20.917
How will they attack? And what happens
when you actually get hit?

00:03:21.717 --> 00:03:22.717
Right.
Minamikawa.

00:03:23.277 --> 00:03:25.257
Yes.
How are you feeling right now?

00:03:25.577 --> 00:03:29.057
Honestly...
You mean in here? Inside the arena?

00:03:30.278 --> 00:03:32.438
I'm terrified.
Absolutely terrified.

00:03:32.438 --> 00:03:36.978
I'm really scared. This just feels wrong,
holding one of these.

00:03:36.978 --> 00:03:43.859
Seriously, seeing that in your face like
that is bad. Yeah, it's scary.

00:03:44.819 --> 00:03:46.359
Now then, Shinichi.
Yeah.

00:03:46.539 --> 00:03:52.299
How about you? I've never done martial
arts, so just being in this space is making my heart race.

00:03:52.639 --> 00:03:53.759
Ah, right, right.
But...

00:03:54.520 --> 00:03:57.700
