finally get to beat someone up.

00:03:57.720 --> 00:04:01.240
Like, all right, let's do this. You don't
usually get a chance to throw hands.

00:04:01.510 --> 00:04:02.510
I see.
Right.

00:04:02.880 --> 00:04:07.240
Officiating the match is Yoshinori Umeki,
well known from Pancrase and K-1.

00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:08.740
Thank you for having me.
This is legit.

00:04:09.080 --> 00:04:11.160
Can he even officiate this?
All right, everyone...

00:04:11.240 --> 00:04:13.501
Here we go.
Can't wait.

00:04:13.501 --> 00:04:16.141
Let's get started. Please.
Go, go, go!

00:04:16.141 --> 00:04:18.621
Do your best.
Face each other.

00:04:19.441 --> 00:04:20.661
Whoa, scary.
Bow to each other.

00:04:21.161 --> 00:04:24.001
All right, it's about to start.
Set.

00:04:25.341 --> 00:04:27.061
This could be over in an instant.
Whoa.

00:04:27.061 --> 00:04:29.221
Whoa, what is this?
You can hear the crackling electricity.

00:04:29.661 --> 00:04:30.661
Fight.
Whoa.

00:04:31.241 --> 00:04:34.241
Hold on a second.
This is the dawn of history.

00:04:35.341 --> 00:04:41.102
This is the first match in a brand-new
sport. Ah, I see, Shinichi's circling.

00:04:41.462 --> 00:04:43.702
Minamikawa is pressuring him.
You can't get close, can you?

00:04:43.742 --> 00:04:47.462
Whoa.
Shinichi is circling, using his feet.

00:04:47.542 --> 00:04:51.422
Right, right. Where do you go for it? The
legs? The shoulder?

00:04:51.422 --> 00:04:52.942
Whoa, he's closing in.
Yeah, he's closing in.

00:04:53.282 --> 00:04:55.362
He's reaching with the lead hand.
Scary, scary.

00:04:55.362 --> 00:04:58.062
He's closing the distance. Minamikawa is
posting that lead hand and applying pressure.

00:04:58.242 --> 00:04:59.242
Scary, scary.
You can do it, you can do it.

00:04:59.242 --> 00:05:01.723
Whoa.
Shinichi throws a feint.

00:05:02.363 --> 00:05:04.203
Wow, this is great.
This is a good match.

00:05:04.903 --> 00:05:06.583
Just watching this is already amazing.
You can do it.

00:05:06.583 --> 00:05:12.343
Scary. The distance between them is
starting to close.

00:05:13.483 --> 00:05:15.623
He's staying low. Shinichi is keeping low.
Yeah.

00:05:16.343 --> 00:05:21.343
So Minamikawa can maybe use his lead hand
to parry it away like this. He's having trouble attacking.

00:05:21.403 --> 00:05:24.004
Yeah.
Or bat it away,

00:05:24.804 --> 00:05:26.444
something like that, maybe.
Oh!

00:05:26.444 --> 00:05:29.664
Minamikawa goes back to the lead hand.
What'll he do?

00:05:30.284 --> 00:05:34.544
Pressure again - the distance is closing.
Shinichi's got the cage at his back.

00:05:34.704 --> 00:05:37.324
Ah, dangerous.
Showing your back is bad.

00:05:37.564 --> 00:05:39.444
It's bad if he shows his back here.
It is.

00:05:39.744 --> 00:05:40.784
Oh.
Oh, careful.

00:05:41.444 --> 00:05:43.324
It's okay.
He's staying low.

00:05:43.544 --> 00:05:46.184
Shinichi keeps that low, tackle-like
stance. Everyone around them...

00:05:46.184 --> 00:05:47.785
What a match.
Scary.

00:05:47.785 --> 00:05:50.945
Great match.
Looking good.

00:05:51.505 --> 00:05:56.105
They've called a brief break. They're so
focused, this could get exhausting if it drags on.

00:05:56.105 --> 00:05:58.605
This looks exhausting.
