So Ungirls still doesn't do the agency
shows anymore? We do.

00:26:49.460 --> 00:26:51.820
Oh, no, I mean us younger guys.
Hah!

00:26:51.820 --> 00:26:54.440
The conversation got interrupted.
The younger guys, right.

00:26:54.520 --> 00:26:58.440
To younger guys, Ungirls counts as within
ten years, within ten years. Yamane closes the distance.

00:26:58.700 --> 00:27:01.240
He's not engaging with the conversation at
all. No, not at all.

00:27:01.340 --> 00:27:04.500
Well, he doesn't need to play along with
that anyway. Right.

00:27:04.600 --> 00:27:06.020
He's completely unfazed.
This is work.

00:27:06.440 --> 00:27:09.500
Osaki's strategy isn't working.
Osaki's strategy isn't working at all.

00:27:10.140 --> 00:27:13.121
Yamane just keeps pressing forward.
That reach is getting in there.

00:27:13.181 --> 00:27:16.061
His reach is so long, so long.
Yeah, that reach is scary.

00:27:16.501 --> 00:27:18.781
Look at his legs.
The senior guy isn't rattled at all.

00:27:18.901 --> 00:27:20.581
Hang in there.
The veteran isn't shaken - Yamane.

00:27:20.941 --> 00:27:22.641
Seriously, wow.
He's tall.

00:27:22.641 --> 00:27:23.601
Listen to me here.
Ah.

00:27:23.601 --> 00:27:27.501
He's really so long, I can't get inside.
Listen to me.

00:27:27.881 --> 00:27:31.021
If this goes on forever, do the batteries
start running down? Ah.

00:27:31.461 --> 00:27:33.561
Huh, has it gotten weaker?
Oh!

00:27:33.581 --> 00:27:35.461
Ah, careful.
Osaki makes his move.

00:27:35.501 --> 00:27:39.162
Ah, he got him down.
Yamane went down - he got stunned.

00:27:39.302 --> 00:27:40.302
Ow!
That looked painful.

00:27:40.302 --> 00:27:41.302
Dirty.
He got him.

00:27:41.542 --> 00:27:44.302
Dirty.
Osaki, that was dirty.

00:27:44.302 --> 00:27:46.242
That was dirty.
That was dirty.

00:27:46.362 --> 00:27:48.942
What the hell, man?!
No, that was dirty.

00:27:48.942 --> 00:27:51.722
What kind of move was that?
That goes against the way of the stun gun.

00:27:52.222 --> 00:27:53.502
The way of the stun gun.
Dirty.

00:27:54.262 --> 00:27:58.222
That was allowed. The referee hadn't
stepped in to stop it yet.

00:27:58.462 --> 00:28:02.342
He was checking whether the current was
flowing, checking the current. Checking the current.

00:28:02.342 --> 00:28:05.323
Ah, he turned around. So he dove in while
the current was running?

00:28:05.393 --> 00:28:06.393
Whoa.
Ah, he flinched.

00:28:07.123 --> 00:28:08.123
Ah, right here.
Careful.

00:28:08.123 --> 00:28:11.103
That hit.
He stumbled.

00:28:11.403 --> 00:28:13.523
Did he get him?
He got him twice.

00:28:13.763 --> 00:28:15.323
No, no - three times.
Three times.

00:28:15.783 --> 00:28:17.763
One more time.
Whoa.

00:28:17.963 --> 00:28:22.283
He's still going. Yamane had already taken
one to the chest before he fell.

00:28:22.643 --> 00:28:28.063
Right, he took one to the chest and went
down. Then just when he thought, "Oh no, I got hit," he got stabbed in the butt too.

00:28:28.283 --> 00:28:31.664
And then in the heel too.
Three times.

00:28:31.684 --> 00:28:34.304
What a psycho. Man, I guess this kind of
thing can happen too.

00:28:34.404 --> 00:28:39.604
Some are saying that goes against the way
of the stun gun. But he didn't miss that split-second opening.

00:28:39.804 --> 00:28:41.804
Yeah, but it was legal under the rules,
wasn't it? Yeah.

00:28:41.804 --> 00:28:45.364
The referee hadn't stopped it, so it was
okay to keep going. Right, yes.

00:28:45.624 --> 00:28:49.424
I don't think it broke any rules. That guy
strayed from the way of Sports Stun Gun.

00:28:49.824 --> 00:28:55.764
He's gone against the way of Sports Stun
Gun. Even that kind of yelling goes against the way of Sports Stun Gun.

00:28:55.914 --> 00:28:56.914
So that's what it was.

00:28:57.645 --> 00:29:03.525
And with that, the 1st Sports Stun Gun
Tournament has just one match left: the final.

00:29:04.325 --> 00:29:06.105
But before that...

00:29:07.245 --> 00:29:13.305
All right, the final is coming up next,
but before that, we'd like to hold an exhibition match.

00:29:13.305 --> 00:29:15.985
W-W-Wait, what? An exhibition?
Hey, wait a second, wait a second.

00:29:17.725 --> 00:29:21.925
Leaving after getting hit with a stun gun
just once feels a little... No, that's more than enough.

00:29:22.705 --> 00:29:24.486
It's plenty.
Too little screen time.

00:29:24.486 --> 00:29:28.026
No, it's enough. I'll work hard from the
sidelines. We seriously don't need this.

00:29:28.386 --> 00:29:30.766
Now listen carefully about this
exhibition. What, what, what?

00:29:31.546 --> 00:29:32.966
We're going to have six people enter the
cage. Whoa!

00:29:33.966 --> 00:29:35.346
What?!
W-W-Wait.

00:29:35.706 --> 00:29:37.586
What kind of gathering is this?

00:29:41.722 --> 00:29:43.302
We'll have six people enter.
Yay!

00:29:43.342 --> 00:29:45.922
And then...
Only one person...

00:29:47.522 --> 00:29:49.062
Huh?
...survives in a battle royale.

00:29:49.185 --> 00:29:50.399
A battle royale.
A battle royale.

00:29:51.042 --> 00:29:53.683
We do not need that.
That's the exhibition we'd like to do.

00:29:53.763 --> 00:29:55.223
Ugh, the worst.
It's a match.

00:29:55.283 --> 00:30:00.063
So then, everyone except the two
finalists, please enter the ring. This is the worst.

00:30:01.123 --> 00:30:04.583
Seriously? And does the last one standing
win anything?

00:30:05.380 --> 00:30:06.963
People will go, "Wow." What the hell kind
of prize is that?! Ah! Ah!

00:30:06.963 --> 00:30:11.203
I want that "wow," though.
Seriously.

00:30:11.303 --> 00:30:14.944
I was told it was just one time.
Quit screwing around!

00:30:15.084 --> 00:30:17.344
Now then, the six men are facing each
other inside the cage.

00:30:17.764 --> 00:30:22.584
Each of them is holding a stun gun. At
this point, you could practically call it a fight to the death.

00:30:23.024 --> 00:30:27.084
What kind of match will this turn into?
Let's work with Blue for now.

00:30:27.304 --> 00:30:30.384
We'll take out the two on Red first.
Hey, hey, hey, no fair.

00:30:30.404 --> 00:30:35.165
No, no, no, seriously, not like that.
Let's do this without any betrayals, please.

00:30:35.305 --> 00:30:36.685
I trust you.
I trust you.

00:30:36.845 --> 00:30:39.365
Don't do it.
All right then, let's begin.

00:30:39.445 --> 00:30:40.785
No, no.
Let's do three on three for now.

00:30:40.785 --> 00:30:41.665
Three on three.
Three on three.

00:30:41.665 --> 00:30:45.125
No, no, no. For now we're allies.
For now, allies.

00:30:45.325 --> 00:30:49.545
For now, allies. No, no, no, that's cheap.
Two against four is cheap. Two against four is cheap.

00:30:49.845 --> 00:30:51.865
Shinichi, please be quiet.
Okay.

00:30:52.465 --> 00:30:54.785
All right, we're starting.
Referee.

00:30:54.995 --> 00:30:55.995
Everyone.
Bow.

00:30:56.505 --> 00:30:58.266
Please.
Set.

00:30:59.563 --> 00:31:01.206
Start!
Teams, teams, teams, teams!

00:31:01.206 --> 00:31:05.426
And we're underway. Maybe we should call
this Ultimate Stun Gun.

00:31:05.586 --> 00:31:09.406
Let's make teams.
Shinichi says we should team up.

00:31:09.726 --> 00:31:13.126
Stop, stop, stop! Stop!
Let's go for Red, Red.

00:31:13.506 --> 00:31:15.026
There are fewer on Red.
I see.

00:31:15.026 --> 00:31:19.987
And now we've got a four-on-two situation.
Stop, stop, stop! Red, Red, Red, Red!

00:31:20.327 --> 00:31:21.667
Tsuda-san, Tsuda-san.
What's he going to do?

00:31:22.447 --> 00:31:23.627
What will the two on Red do?
Ah!

00:31:24.027 --> 00:31:28.667
Now Tsuda makes his move.

00:31:29.127 --> 00:31:32.387
The two on Red.
He betrayed them.

00:31:32.427 --> 00:31:35.667
An unbelievable betrayal.
Tani betrayed them.

00:31:36.367 --> 00:31:38.627
Tani's betrayal.
What the hell, man?

00:31:38.627 --> 00:31:44.848
No, no, no. Hold on, hold on.
And now Michio goes in.

00:31:44.848 --> 00:31:49.508
Ah, that guy.
Whoa, Tsuda - Tsuda's out of there.

00:31:50.028 --> 00:31:51.308
Tani.
Three of them have Michio cornered.

00:31:51.608 --> 00:31:53.588
Ah!
Payback.

00:31:53.588 --> 00:31:56.428
Mr. Yamane.
Tani is strong. Tani's got two of them.

00:31:57.088 --> 00:31:59.328
Mr. Yamane, wait a second.
Mr. Yamane, wait a second.

00:31:59.608 --> 00:32:02.469
Hold on, hold on. And just like that,
three men are already out.

00:32:02.929 --> 00:32:06.529
That leaves three.
Tani is moving surprisingly well.

00:32:06.809 --> 00:32:12.529
That push-back we saw in round one is
showing itself again. Mr. Yamane has a ton of energy left right now.

00:32:13.169 --> 00:32:16.069
Trust me.
I've still got a lot left in the tank.

00:32:16.289 --> 00:32:17.449
Seriously, let's do this right here.

00:32:17.449 --> 00:32:22.610
No, no, no. Tani's really - Tani's
honestly got a terrible personality. No, you're the one!

00:32:23.950 --> 00:32:28.250
Then Mr. Yamane, Mr. Yamane - Tani is
seriously dangerous. He'll really do it, for real.

00:32:28.610 --> 00:32:30.110
No, no.
What do we do?

00:32:30.610 --> 00:32:33.010
It's like a negotiation now.
He may be getting a little cocky.

00:32:33.030 --> 00:32:35.610
I'm sorry.
Mr. Yamane.

00:32:36.770 --> 00:32:39.490
You don't need "may be" - just call him
cocky. A triangle formation has taken shape.

00:32:40.050 --> 00:32:42.130
It all depends on what Mr. Yamane does.
Mr. Yamane, come up behind him.

00:32:42.150 --> 00:32:46.151
Tani closes the distance. If Yamane gets
behind either one of them, he's got a shot.

00:32:46.171 --> 00:32:52.331
True, true. Mr. Yamane, seriously - I
really do listen to your radio show.

00:32:53.091 --> 00:32:58.271
I seriously listen to your radio show, Mr.
Yamane. He's lying. He doesn't listen to your show, Mr. Yamane.

00:32:58.491 --> 00:33:00.591
Mr. Yamane, you have a radio show?
I do, I do.

00:33:00.911 --> 00:33:02.791
Ah, that wasn't good, was it, Tani?

00:33:02.811 --> 00:33:07.392
Mr. Yamane, I really listen to your show -
your show is seriously funny. What's it like? What's it like?

00:33:07.612 --> 00:33:13.332
It's great - Fukawa Ryo was on it just the
other day. Okay.

00:33:13.332 --> 00:33:16.772
Ah, it's decided. Now it's two on one. Has
Tani been trapped?

00:33:17.152 --> 00:33:18.912
His face just changed.
This isn't good odds for him.

00:33:19.472 --> 00:33:23.652
He's badly outnumbered.
Now it's become a two-on-one setup.

00:33:24.192 --> 00:33:27.713
But from Tani's point of view, if he can
take out one of them... Right, then he can make it one on one.

00:33:28.873 --> 00:33:31.573
So Tani's plan is to target Shinichi
first. He's going in.

00:33:31.573 --> 00:33:35.693
This is bad, bad.
Tani's getting worn out now, seriously.

00:33:36.033 --> 00:33:40.733
He already took out Michio and Shogo,
after all. He took down two guys by himself.

00:33:40.733 --> 00:33:43.133
Honestly, I've got this easy right now.
Let's move back to the middle once.

00:33:43.473 --> 00:33:47.573
No, shut up! You shut up!
Seriously, please just shut up.

00:33:47.913 --> 00:33:50.354
Seriously.
Seriously, you - look at that.

00:33:50.574 --> 00:33:53.454
We're not getting anywhere. One hit with
the stun gun... No, wait for him to come from behind.

00:33:54.134 --> 00:33:57.474
Mr. Yamane.
This is really the kind of person he is.

00:33:57.514 --> 00:34:01.966
This is bad, bad - Tani's in trouble.
Tani's coming out, coming out.

00:34:02.186 --> 00:34:04.306
Ah, here he comes, here he comes!
He's just got to go for it now.

00:34:04.866 --> 00:34:08.306
The distance is closing.
Tani advances with his wrist trembling.

00:34:08.426 --> 00:34:12.987
Oh, oh, oh, oh.
The distance is closing.

00:34:12.987 --> 00:34:14.787
Two on one.
Shinichi - Shinichi's been caught.

00:34:15.407 --> 00:34:16.947
Two against one.
Ah, he betrayed him.

00:34:17.187 --> 00:34:19.627
And here's Yamane's betrayal.
Nicely done.

00:34:20.207 --> 00:34:25.567
Yamane betrayed Shinichi.
So that's how this is going, huh?

00:34:27.047 --> 00:34:30.648
Well, of course he didn't want to get hit
with that. Scary.

00:34:31.308 --> 00:34:35.848
He's the bad guy here after all, isn't he?
Him, right? He never really thought my radio show was funny.

00:34:36.568 --> 00:34:38.628
Battle royale.
And now it's down to one on one.

00:34:39.708 --> 00:34:44.048
Ah, the crouching strategy. Yeah, the
crouching strategy worked once already.

00:34:44.128 --> 00:34:49.769
Tani may have gone out in round one, but
in this battle royale... ...he's really showing his strength.

00:34:49.809 --> 00:34:52.089
What the hell is that supposed to mean?
No shots to the face, okay?

00:34:52.889 --> 00:34:55.329
No shots to the face, okay?
Yeah, no face shots, but still...

00:34:55.669 --> 00:34:57.709
No face shots.
This format might just suit him.

00:34:58.649 --> 00:35:01.589
I see. By crouching, he makes his target
area smaller.

00:35:03.349 --> 00:35:06.090
He's reducing the surface area that can be
hit. That reach is long.

00:35:06.090 --> 00:35:08.490
I see.
But that sliding step gets tiring.

00:35:08.490 --> 00:35:13.850
That forward-leaning stance. Still, I feel
like Tani is starting to enjoy this a little.

00:35:13.970 --> 00:35:16.390
True - you can see it in his face now,
he's smiling. This fight to the death.

00:35:17.030 --> 00:35:20.730
Stun-guns high.
He's totally on a stun-gun high now.

00:35:20.730 --> 00:35:24.931
What is this?
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

00:35:24.951 --> 00:35:27.031
Did that do it?
Wow, he's not scared at all.

00:35:27.991 --> 00:35:30.891
What do you mean, "that's what this is"?
What is this?

00:35:30.991 --> 00:35:35.471
He's walking while staying crouched.
Yamane is using that reach...

00:35:35.511 --> 00:35:40.472
Ah! Yamane finishes him with that long
reach. Yamane is strong.

00:35:40.652 --> 00:35:44.812
And the last shot was a straight right.
It's all about the reach, the reach.

00:35:44.812 --> 00:35:49.352
Yamane's reach carried him to victory.

00:35:49.852 --> 00:35:54.012
Whoa, that battle royale really had all
kinds of... well...

00:35:54.812 --> 00:36:00.253
It gave us some real drama. The moment the
two-against-one situation on Tani suddenly flipped...

00:36:00.953 --> 00:36:03.653
That was fun.
From both sides.

00:36:03.873 --> 00:36:04.873
Right?
Like, "Ahhh!"

00:36:05.073 --> 00:36:08.053
You suddenly get all these human dynamics.
And betrayals.

00:36:08.713 --> 00:36:14.113
And Shogo too - at first it looked like
he'd team up with Tani, but he got betrayed instantly. Exactly.

00:36:14.754 --> 00:36:16.054
Has anyone ever been this pitiful?

00:36:17.134 --> 00:36:22.654
Well, I made the first move because I
wanted to break up the Blue team first.

00:36:22.914 --> 00:36:25.534
Then from behind, this red, super-fast
guy...

00:36:26.594 --> 00:36:31.314
...came after my shoulder. It happened in
an instant. It hurt like hell.

00:36:31.514 --> 00:36:34.235
It was crazy, right? And after that, Tsuda
got targeted too, right?

00:36:34.595 --> 00:36:36.835
Michio just came charging straight at me.

00:36:37.555 --> 00:36:43.415
And the scary thing was, I couldn't dodge
him. He was like a dump truck.

00:36:43.475 --> 00:36:47.815
But then Michio got taken out by Tani too.
Yeah, he got hit from behind.

00:36:48.155 --> 00:36:49.235
Right?
Yeah.

00:36:49.815 --> 00:36:50.836
All right, Yamane.
Yes.

00:36:51.056 --> 00:36:54.556
Congratulations.
Thank you very much.

00:36:54.556 --> 00:36:57.396
What even was that?
What was that?

00:36:57.916 --> 00:37:00.816
Give me something, anything.
That was just infighting, seriously.

00:37:01.996 --> 00:37:07.196
All right, all right.
Don't "all right, all right" me.

00:37:07.316 --> 00:37:10.577
And now, Sports Stun Gun heads at last
into the final.

00:37:12.997 --> 00:37:18.997
Minamikawa versus Japan's Funniest Osaki.
Which one will become the inaugural champion?

00:37:18.997 --> 00:37:21.477
Mr. Minamikawa!
Mr. Minamikawa!

00:37:21.697 --> 00:37:24.137
Mr. Minamikawa, go!
Minamikawa!

00:37:24.557 --> 00:37:28.338
Mr. Minamikawa! Funny thing is, now that
we've made it to the final, these two really do have a different aura.

00:37:28.858 --> 00:37:32.318
It really feels like two strong guys are
standing there. Yeah.

00:37:32.958 --> 00:37:35.718
It really makes you want to know who's
strongest. I want to see it.

00:37:36.178 --> 00:37:37.598
Shinichi's a little fired up too.

00:37:37.898 --> 00:37:42.078
Yeah, because he faced Mr. Minamikawa in
round one, so he really wants him to win it all. I see.

00:37:43.618 --> 00:37:47.339
That does happen, right? You want to feel
like the guy who beat you was actually strong.

00:37:47.899 --> 00:37:51.059
Osaki beat us, but we still want Osaki to
lose. Hey, hold on.

00:37:51.639 --> 00:37:54.739
Yeah, I can't root for that guy.
All right then, let's get to the final.

00:37:54.819 --> 00:37:56.719
All right!
Let's do this.

00:37:57.139 --> 00:37:59.559
Bow to each other.
Please.

00:37:59.579 --> 00:38:04.300
All right, here we go.
Please.

00:38:04.300 --> 00:38:04.840
Take your stance.
Fight!

00:38:04.840 --> 00:38:09.000
And we're off. The winner becomes the
first-ever champion.

00:38:09.180 --> 00:38:13.020
Oh, is he going to carry him?
Fight!

00:38:13.420 --> 00:38:15.280
Yeah, yeah.
He's got him cornered.

00:38:15.280 --> 00:38:16.800
Go, Mr. Minamikawa.
Keep your eyes on him.

00:38:16.900 --> 00:38:19.280
Mr. Minamikawa, go!
Minamikawa's really good at this.

00:38:19.501 --> 00:38:25.241
That reach. The winner will earn the same
kind of honor as Royce Gracie.

00:38:25.681 --> 00:38:30.461
After all, being the first champion of a
tournament like this means your name goes down in history. Exactly.

00:38:30.501 --> 00:38:34.701
No, with combat sports... Minamikawa opens
with the lead hand and applies pressure.

00:38:34.821 --> 00:38:37.982
His footwork is good.
The way his feet stay loose.

00:38:38.982 --> 00:38:43.182
This... But Osaki originally played
catcher in baseball.

00:38:43.182 --> 00:38:44.539
He's confident in his reflexes.
Speed.

00:38:50.686 --> 00:38:52.806
Talk while you do it.
Oh, he's coming in.

00:38:53.666 --> 00:38:55.506
Mr. Minamikawa, stay with it.
Oh!

00:38:55.686 --> 00:38:57.646
Osaki is trying to throw him off.
Yeah.

00:38:59.667 --> 00:39:03.267
Go high, high, make it big.
Careful, he's going for the hand.

00:39:03.587 --> 00:39:05.967
Oh, didn't he hit his hand?
He did, he did, he did!

00:39:06.027 --> 00:39:07.447
The electricity's running, electricity!
Ah, man.

00:39:07.707 --> 00:39:10.347
He did it again, again.
He's going for the cheap shot.

00:39:10.507 --> 00:39:14.108
Ah, he went for another cheap shot too.
Just like in the semifinal, he's going for surprise attacks.

00:39:14.568 --> 00:39:20.468
Now's the moment, now's the moment.
Minamikawa's eyes just changed.

00:39:20.568 --> 00:39:24.248
Even in a technical match like this...
...the switch just flipped.

00:39:24.668 --> 00:39:27.708
Minamikawa's killer switch just flipped.
He's going no-guard - incredible.

00:39:27.908 --> 00:39:29.509
He's aiming for the face.
That's dirty.

00:39:29.509 --> 00:39:35.649
That dirty tactic from earlier...
...flipped the switch.

00:39:35.649 --> 00:39:38.089
Osaki goes for the same surprise attack as
before. Hey.

00:39:39.189 --> 00:39:40.529
No, this...
Oh!

00:39:40.889 --> 00:39:43.389
Ah, he turned his back.
He's arching away.

00:39:44.029 --> 00:39:47.090
Osaki turns his back on his opponent.
This is very tricky...

00:39:47.590 --> 00:39:51.270
A tricky strategy.
Osaki's gone no-guard now.

00:39:51.670 --> 00:39:53.670
Ah, he swung behind his back.
With a backhand.

00:39:54.710 --> 00:39:56.550
He went with a backhand.
That doesn't do anything.

00:39:57.130 --> 00:39:58.230
Don't look.
Oh.

00:39:58.930 --> 00:40:00.511
Ah, he's not tired.
He's leaning against the cage.

00:40:00.571 --> 00:40:02.971
No, is he baiting him in?
Me?

00:40:02.971 --> 00:40:03.971
Ah, careful.
Whoa.

00:40:04.111 --> 00:40:07.831
Ah, that landed.
Which one was it?

00:40:07.911 --> 00:40:09.131
Which one?
Which one?

00:40:09.131 --> 00:40:10.831
Stop, stop, stop!
It landed a second ago, didn't it?

00:40:10.831 --> 00:40:11.731
Which one?
Which one was it?

00:40:11.731 --> 00:40:12.711
Huh? What happened?
Which one?

00:40:12.711 --> 00:40:14.771
But Osaki's still standing.
Osaki's still standing.

00:40:14.971 --> 00:40:16.512
Wait a second.
Osaki's still standing.

00:40:16.812 --> 00:40:20.912
Osaki didn't get hit?
Why is Osaki still standing?

00:40:23.772 --> 00:40:26.732
Osaki didn't get hit?
Huh?

00:40:27.012 --> 00:40:29.812
I haven't felt any pain.
No way.

00:40:30.372 --> 00:40:32.173
Let's check the VTR.
It hit, right?

00:40:32.173 --> 00:40:37.013
What exactly happened there?
I thought it made pretty solid contact.

00:40:37.093 --> 00:40:39.593
They got tangled up.
He dodged this.

00:40:40.093 --> 00:40:43.153
Ah, it didn't hit.
It missed - no contact.

00:40:43.233 --> 00:40:44.973
So it didn't hit.
His hand kind of...

00:40:45.173 --> 00:40:49.174
The electricity was just conducting
through. His hand was at an angle, so maybe it never fully connected.

00:40:49.544 --> 00:40:50.544
Ah.
And then this...

00:40:50.614 --> 00:40:53.674
Didn't it hit his butt?
Where did Minamikawa get hit?

00:40:53.814 --> 00:40:55.034
So he did get hit.
Right here.

00:40:55.134 --> 00:40:57.494
The heart, and...
...the heart and the butt.

00:40:57.614 --> 00:41:02.014
He got hit twice.
Twice?

00:41:02.054 --> 00:41:04.155
Twice.
This guy again...

00:41:04.295 --> 00:41:08.055
While they were tangled up.
Ah, that's where one of them landed.

00:41:08.375 --> 00:41:11.115
Right here. And after this, you think it's
going to the back...

00:41:11.595 --> 00:41:13.715
No, that didn't hit.
It goes to the butt.

00:41:15.375 --> 00:41:16.375
Strong.
Ah.

00:41:16.775 --> 00:41:17.776
Amazing.
Osaki.

00:41:18.756 --> 00:41:20.096
That was incredible from Osaki.
Seriously.

00:41:20.496 --> 00:41:23.016
Even while falling down...
...while tangled up.

00:41:23.376 --> 00:41:25.756
What a move.
Wow, what an exchange.

00:41:26.036 --> 00:41:29.316
A final worthy of the name.
Yeah, it was high-level stuff.

00:41:29.336 --> 00:41:32.876
Damn it. Has there ever been a champion
who felt this unsatisfying?

00:41:32.876 --> 00:41:36.377
Why did that guy have to win?
Nobody can root for you.

00:41:36.377 --> 00:41:42.497
And with that, the winner is...
Japan's Funniest Osaki.

00:41:42.617 --> 00:41:46.277
I can't accept this.

00:41:48.697 --> 00:41:54.278
That last match was amazing, but Osaki...
...won the whole thing without getting hit even once.

00:41:54.498 --> 00:41:56.618
That's right.
Exactly.

00:41:57.978 --> 00:42:00.178
Does it hurt?
Man, that's irritating.

00:42:01.358 --> 00:42:04.258
Why did a guy like that have to win?
Minamikawa came so close.

00:42:04.559 --> 00:42:07.379
He really did. If there's a second one, I
absolutely want to win it.

00:42:07.759 --> 00:42:10.539
You wanted that first-ever title, didn't
you? You lost hard.

00:42:10.779 --> 00:42:13.499
Wow, this really is frustrating.

00:42:13.499 --> 00:42:18.679
Honestly, I thought this even before we
started, but this really is like a real combat sport. Yeah, it really is close.

00:42:18.679 --> 00:42:20.580
This is unbelievably frustrating.
It's incredible.

00:42:21.100 --> 00:42:23.720
So everybody wants to do it again, right?
Tsuda, you'd want back in too if there's a second one, right?

00:42:25.020 --> 00:42:26.020
I do...
No way.

00:42:26.800 --> 00:42:28.320
Really?
I'll train up again from here.

00:42:28.580 --> 00:42:32.760
Tsuda said fencing would give him a
special advantage, but it didn't help at all. Not one bit.

00:42:32.760 --> 00:42:35.200
What?
Not one bit.

00:42:35.781 --> 00:42:40.141
Still, if you brought in an active fencer,
they'd probably be strong at this. Yeah, maybe.

00:42:40.421 --> 00:42:41.941
Please make it a little longer next time.

00:42:44.401 --> 00:42:51.401
After this, let's all throw around some
ideas.

00:42:53.742 --> 00:42:55.922
Make it better.

00:42:55.982 --> 00:43:02.682
Make it even better.
Like tackles.

00:43:02.802 --> 00:43:03.982
Tackles.
Ah, that's good.

00:43:04.422 --> 00:43:06.683
Now all kinds of ideas are coming out.
This segment really works.

00:43:09.563 --> 00:43:14.763
And with that, we'll see you again someday
for the second tournament. Osaki is the champion.

00:43:14.823 --> 00:43:20.963
Congratulations.

00:43:21.143 --> 00:43:24.464
All right!
Goodbye.

00:43:24.464 --> 00:43:25.364
I really can't argue with it.
